      <body>
         <div type="poem"
              xml:id="txt_GrayTh1716_sng1"
              corresp="authors.xml#txt_GrayTh1716_sng1"
              subtype="eceptext"
              rendition="#lgvspace"
              rhyme="aa"
              met="-+|--+|--+|--+-/"
              n="12"
              ana="#tetrameter #couplet #anapaest #catalexis #hypercatalexis">
            <link type="author" target="authors.xml#aut_GrayTh1716"/>
            <head>Song I</head>
            <lg n="1">
               <l n="1">'Midst beauty and pleasure's gay triumphs, to languish</l>
               <l n="2">And droop without knowing the source of my anguish;</l>
               <l n="3">To start from short slumbers and look for the morning---</l>
               <l n="4">Yet close my dull eyes when I see it returning;</l>
            </lg>
            <lg n="2">
               <l n="5">Sighs sudden and frequent, looks ever dejected,</l>
               <l n="6">Sounds that steal from my tongue, by no meaning connected!</l>
               <l n="7">Ah say, fellow-swains, how these symptoms befell me?</l>
               <l n="8">They smile, but reply not. Sure Delia will tell me!</l>
            </lg>
         </div>
